<div>Here's some easy music notation!</div>
<div id="easyScore"></div>

<div>FLAT API</div>
<div>
  <div>Cool features: </div>
  <ul> 
    <li>It will play easily with: adjustable speed, fullscreen option, metronome capabilities, volume control, print capabilities</li>
    <li>you can edit it in any way really, and then when you reload it resets</li>
    <li>Can easily change size/location using the api</li>
    <li>Really easy to use (autogenerated html to embed, try inspecting element)</li>
  </ul> 
  <div>Drawbacks of free flat api </div>
  <ul>
    <li>Ugly logo that you can only get rid of if you pay</li>
    <li>Can only do 15 scores per web app in the free version (likely gonna be a problem)</li>
    <li>Limit of 10,000 views/month (prob not an issue)</li>
    <li>limit of 100 active users for editing/month (prob not an issue)</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div>Disclaimer: this is an arrangement I made for my hs acapella group using flat as a music composition software, don't judge ;)</div>
<div id="embed-container"></div>
<script src="https://prod.flat-cdn.com/embed-js/v1.3.0/embed.min.js"></script>
<script>
  var container = document.getElementById("embed-container");
  var embed = new Flat.Embed(container, {
    "width": "100%",
    "height": "700",
    "score": "577084505d28249848a68661",
    "embedParams": {
      "mode": "edit",
      "appId": "5f31d0690692f8689b6682fb"
    },
  });
  // You can now use the `embed` instance.
  // Check out the docs at https://flat.io/developers/docs/embed/javascript.html
</script>
